HEADWORD: Caddice fly
<hw>Caddice fly</hw> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <def>a small mothlike species
of trichopterous insect, whose larva is the caddice; it has two pairs of
hairy membranous wings and aquatic larvae.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caddie</ent>⟦br⟧
